message.content:
1. At 18 months, HA1 had the highest improvement in total WOMAC with a 65.20% reduction.
2. At 18 months, PRP had a 55.01% reduction in total WOMAC.
3. At 18 months, HA3 had a 49.57% reduction in total WOMAC.
4. At 18 months, HA2 had a 29.82% reduction in total WOMAC.
5. The control group had a 14.55% increase in total WOMAC over baseline at 18 months.
6. There was a significant difference (p=0.001) in total WOMAC between the control group and HA1 at 18 months.
7. There was a significant difference (p=0.001) in total WOMAC between the control group and HA3 at 18 months.
